===message:David that is an interesting thought.  I too wonder if this was planned.  At the Yalta Conference tensions started rising when Stalin ensured that the Red Army's presence would dictate the future of states liberated by the Soviets (pg 1063).  Because the United States and Britain wanted Stalin to help them in the war against Japan and to collaborate in the establishment of the United Nations, Roosevelt and Churchill gave into Stalin.  I felt like the war against Japan could have been won without the Russian alliance.  I am with you on the created tension.
